# Day 15 – CloudFront Basics & Troubleshooting

## Goal
Learn how CloudFront delivers content from S3 securely and troubleshoot common errors.

## Steps
- Created CloudFront distribution with S3 origin.
- Tested access via CloudFront domain.
- Simulated AccessDenied by removing bucket public access.
- Configured Origin Access Control (OAC).
- Updated bucket policy to allow CloudFront OAC.
- Retested → CloudFront served files successfully.

## Lessons Learned
- CloudFront caches and distributes content globally.
- OAC allows secure access to private S3 buckets.
- Common error: AccessDenied when bucket policy is missing.
- Fix: configure OAC + correct bucket policy.

